Foam Management and De-aeration
One of the most common failures in home blending is the creation of a thick, frothy "head" of foam.19 This is caused by the entrapment of air during the high-speed vortex phase. To master this, the "Bubble-Pop" technique is employed: after the high-speed cycle is complete, the blender is run at its lowest speed for 20 seconds.55 This allows the large bubbles to coalesce and rise to the surface, resulting in a clearer liquid.56
